<paragraph id="A2443683FFBD411DFCB2AA42E1B4FC9E" blockId="9.[826,1441,1544,1903]" lastBlockId="10.[144,759,699,874]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="157" pageId="9" pageNumber="156">
<emphasis id="908FEA91FFBD411EFCB2AA42E0F2F9EA" box="[826,945,1545,1566]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="156">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Distinguished from all other genera of 
<taxonomicName id="65FB4D00FFBD411EFCEEAA6CE745F9C9" box="[870,1030,1575,1597]" pageId="9" pageNumber="147" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Cynopoecilina">Cynopoecilina</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="65FB4D00FFBD411EFBADAA6CE7E5F9C8" authorityName="Myers" authorityYear="1952" box="[1061,1190,1575,1596]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Leptolebias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="156" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="908FEA91FFBD411EFBADAA6CE7E5F9C8" box="[1061,1190,1575,1596]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="156">Leptolebias</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="65FB4D00FFBD411EFB4CAA6CE61BF9C8" authorityName="Regan" authorityYear="1912" box="[1220,1368,1575,1596]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Cynopoecilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="156" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="908FEA91FFBD411EFB4CAA6CE61BF9C8" box="[1220,1368,1575,1596]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="156">Cynopoecilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="65FB4D00FFBD411EFCB2AA0EE0ABF9AE" box="[826,1000,1605,1626]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Campellolebias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="156" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="908FEA91FFBD411EFCB2AA0EE0ABF9AE" box="[826,1000,1605,1626]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="156">Campellolebias</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) by the possession of dermosphenotic (vs. dermosphenotic absent), basihyal narrow, roughly rectangular (
<figureCitation id="3AC02A06FFBD411EFC56AAC8E75DF96D" box="[990,1054,1667,1689]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="3.[164,243,1409,1428]" captionTargetBox="[388,1218,956,1379]" captionTargetId="figure-470@3.[387,1219,955,1380]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 3. Osteological features in Leptolebias and Notholebias: A, medial portion of hyoid and branchial skeleton, dorsal view, of Leptolebias citrinipinnis. B, medial portion of hyoid and branchial skeleton, dorsal view, of Notholebias fractifasciatus. C, anguloarticular region, left side, lateral view, of L. citrinipinnis. D, jaw suspensorium, left side, lateral view, of N. fractifasciatus. Abbreviations: AA, anguloarticular; B1–B3, basibranchials 1–3; BB, basibranchial cartilage; BC, basihyal cartilage; BH, basihyal; H1–H3, hypobranchials 1–3; HY, hyomandibula; MS, mesopterygoid; MT, metapterygoid; PL, autopalatine; PO, preopercle; QU, quadrate; RA, retroarticular; SY, sympletic. Larger stippling indicates cartilage. Scale bar: 1 mm." pageId="9" pageNumber="156">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) (vs. wide, triangular), welldeveloped contact organs on most inner surface of pectoral fin in males (vs. contact organs reduced or absent), opercular region with red bars in males (
<figureCitation id="3AC02A06FFBD411EFCCAAAB6E0CCF8E7" box="[834,911,1789,1811]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="10.[144,223,539,558]" captionTargetBox="[148,756,197,509]" captionTargetId="figure-703@10.[148,756,197,509]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figure 11. Notholebias minimus, male, not preserved, about 20-mm standard length (1 day after collection); Brazil, Estado do Rio de Janeiro, Seropédica (photo by W. J. E. M. Costa)." pageId="9" pageNumber="156">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
) (vs. red reticulation), and iridescent bars or vertical lines on caudal fin in males (
<figureCitation id="3AC02A06FFBD411EFB6BAB57E673F8C6" box="[1251,1328,1820,1842]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="10.[144,223,539,558]" captionTargetBox="[148,756,197,509]" captionTargetId="figure-703@10.[148,756,197,509]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figure 11. Notholebias minimus, male, not preserved, about 20-mm standard length (1 day after collection); Brazil, Estado do Rio de Janeiro, Seropédica (photo by W. J. E. M. Costa)." pageId="9" pageNumber="156">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
) (vs. bars absent). Also differs from 
<taxonomicName id="65FB4D00FFBD411EFBEEAB71E7A4F8BB" authorityName="Myers" authorityYear="1952" box="[1126,1255,1850,1871]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Leptolebias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="156" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="908FEA91FFBD411EFBEEAB71E7A4F8BB" box="[1126,1255,1850,1871]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="156">Leptolebias</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having teeth on second pharyngobranchial (teeth absent), caudal fin subtruncate to rounded, short, deeper than long (
<figureCitation id="3AC02A06FFBE411DFF10AE91E3A6FD04" box="[152,229,730,752]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="10.[144,223,539,558]" captionTargetBox="[148,756,197,509]" captionTargetId="figure-703@10.[148,756,197,509]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figure 11. Notholebias minimus, male, not preserved, about 20-mm standard length (1 day after collection); Brazil, Estado do Rio de Janeiro, Seropédica (photo by W. J. E. M. Costa)." pageId="10" pageNumber="157">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
) (vs. elliptical to lanceolate, longer than deep), two anterior supraorbital neuromasts (vs. single anterior supraorbital neuromast), and dark pigmentation extending over entire dorsal fin in males (vs. not extending to distal third of dorsal fin).
</paragraph>
<caption id="F684660BFFBE411DFF18AE50E21EFD72" pageId="10" pageNumber="157" startId="10.[144,223,539,558]" targetBox="[148,756,197,509]" targetPageId="10">
<paragraph id="A2443683FFBE411DFF18AE50E21EFD72" blockId="10.[144,759,539,646]" pageId="10" pageNumber="157">
<emphasis id="908FEA91FFBE411DFF18AE50E247FDDA" bold="true" box="[144,260,539,558]" pageId="10" pageNumber="157">Figure 11.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="65FB4D00FFBE411DFE98AE50E2BAFDD9" authorityName="Costa" authorityYear="2008" baseAuthorityName="Myers" baseAuthorityYear="1942" box="[272,505,539,558]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Notholebias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="157" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="minimus">
<emphasis id="908FEA91FFBE411DFE98AE50E2BAFDD9" box="[272,505,539,558]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="157">Notholebias minimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, male, not preserved, about 20-mm standard length (1 day after collection); Brazil, Estado do Rio de Janeiro, Seropédica (photo by W. J. E. M. Costa).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="A2443683FFBE411DFF18AFDDE1A8FC1D" blockId="10.[144,759,918,1002]" pageId="10" pageNumber="157">
<emphasis id="908FEA91FFBE411DFF18AFDDE222FC58" box="[144,353,918,940]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="157">Included species:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="65FB4D00FFBE411DFEF2AFDDE1B3FC58" authority="(Myers)" authorityName="Costa" authorityYear="2008" baseAuthorityName="Myers" baseAuthorityYear="1942" box="[378,752,918,940]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Notholebias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="157" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="minimus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="908FEA91FFBE411DFEF2AFDDE13CFC58" box="[378,639,918,940]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="157">Notholebias minimus</emphasis>
(Myers)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="8BBC57EAFFBE411DFF18AFFEE24BFC3E" box="[144,264,949,971]" pageId="10" pageNumber="157" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
; 
<taxonomicName id="65FB4D00FFBE411DFEB9AFFEE1B4FC3F" authority="(Costa)" authorityName="Costa" authorityYear="2008" baseAuthorityName="Costa" baseAuthorityYear="1988" box="[305,759,949,971]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Notholebias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="157" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fractifasciatus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="908FEA91FFBE411DFEB9AFFEE13CFC3E" box="[305,639,949,970]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="157">Notholebias fractifasciatus</emphasis>
(Costa)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="8BBC57EAFFBE411DFF18AF98E24BFC1D" box="[144,264,979,1001]" pageId="10" pageNumber="157" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
; and 
<taxonomicName id="65FB4D00FFBE411DFEC2AF98E12DFC1E" authority="(Costa)" authorityName="Costa" authorityYear="2008" baseAuthorityName="Costa" box="[330,622,979,1002]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Notholebias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="157" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cruzi" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="908FEA91FFBE411DFEC2AF98E151FC1D" box="[330,530,979,1001]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="157">Notholebias cruzi</emphasis>
(Costa)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="8BBC57EAFFBE411DFDFDAF98E1A8FC1D" box="[629,747,979,1001]" pageId="10" pageNumber="157" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A2443683FFBE411DFF18A85EE2C0FB9C" blockId="10.[144,758,1045,1128]" pageId="10" pageNumber="157">
<emphasis id="908FEA91FFBE411DFF18A85EE262FBDE" box="[144,289,1045,1066]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="157">Distribution:</emphasis>
Coastal plains of south-eastern 
<collectingCountry id="DAEC7613FFBE411DFD22A85EE1B1FBDF" box="[682,754,1045,1067]" name="Brazil" pageId="10" pageNumber="157">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, between the São João river floodplains and Itaguaí, 
<collectingRegion id="603FF861FFBE411DFF18A819E23CFB9C" box="[144,383,1106,1128]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="10" pageNumber="157">Rio de Janeiro state</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A2443683FFBE411DFF18A8DFE15AFA4A" blockId="10.[144,759,1172,1470]" pageId="10" pageNumber="157">
<emphasis id="908FEA91FFBE411DFF18A8DFE24EFB5D" box="[144,269,1172,1193]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="157">Etymology:</emphasis>
The name 
<taxonomicName id="65FB4D00FFBE411DFE16A8DFE167FB5D" authorityName="Costa" authorityYear="2008" box="[414,548,1172,1193]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Notholebias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="157" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="908FEA91FFBE411DFE16A8DFE167FB5D" box="[414,548,1172,1193]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="157">Notholebias</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an allusion to the superficial resemblance between species included in the new genus and some species of the African killifish genus 
<taxonomicName id="65FB4D00FFBE411DFEC8A8BBE1D5FAF2" authority="Peters, 1868" authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1868" box="[320,662,1264,1286]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Nothobranchiidae" genus="Nothobranchius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="157" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="908FEA91FFBE411DFEC8A8BBE2B5FAF1" box="[320,502,1264,1285]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="157">Nothobranchius</emphasis>
Peters, 1868
</taxonomicName>
, in particular 
<taxonomicName id="65FB4D00FFBE411DFF64A944E1B1FAD0" authority="Wildekamp, 1977" authorityName="Wildekamp" authorityYear="1977" box="[236,754,1295,1317]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Nothobranchiidae" genus="Nothobranchius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="157" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lourensi">
<emphasis id="908FEA91FFBE411DFF64A944E14CFAD0" box="[236,527,1295,1316]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="157">Nothobranchius lourensi</emphasis>
Wildekamp, 1977
</taxonomicName>
, which have similar colour patterns and similar body proportions (from the Greek 
<emphasis id="908FEA91FFBE411DFD8AA907E10FFA95" box="[514,588,1356,1377]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="157">nothos</emphasis>
= false, taken from the name 
<taxonomicName id="65FB4D00FFBE411DFEDDA920E148FA74" authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1868" box="[341,523,1387,1408]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Nothobranchiidae" genus="Nothobranchius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="157" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="908FEA91FFBE411DFEDDA920E148FA74" box="[341,523,1387,1408]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="157">Nothobranchius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<emphasis id="908FEA91FFBE411DFDD3A920E1DEFA74" box="[603,669,1387,1408]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="157">lebias</emphasis>
= small fish, a name often used to compose generic names of rivulid fishes). Gender masculine.
</paragraph>
